        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 11:40PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1140 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Lake Mcclellan, or 16 miles south of Pampa, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsmill, Lake Mcclellan, Lefors, Alanreed, Mclean, and Pampa.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 115 and 116, and
between mile markers 131 and 146.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
